{
  "doc_id": "16031",
  "text": "Explicitly treating all phase conversions and including the latent heat of fusion has eliminated the globally averaged energy loss of ϳ0.2 W m Ϫ2 due to inconsistencies between the atmospheric and surface models, discussed by [CITATION_1] and Boville and Bretherton (2003) . The effect of the latent heat of fusion on the CAM3 simulation is relatively modest because the latent heat of fusion is small compared to the latent heat of vaporization. Therefore, adding the heat due to the freezing of cloud condensate modifies the convective heating by Ͻ20%. However, this term might make a larger difference if it was included within the formulation of the convective parameterizations.",
